  <!-- FAQ -->
  <section class="faq">
    <div class="wrap">
      <h2 class="sec-head reveal" style="text-align:center;margin:0 auto;">Frequently asked questions</h2>
      <div class="faq-list" id="faqList">
        <div class="faq-item">
          <div class="faq-q">How long does a project take?<span class="ic">+</span></div>
          <div class="faq-a"><p>Most websites and store revamps take about 2–6 weeks depending on scope, number of pages or products, and how quickly content is ready. We confirm the timeline in your proposal.</p></div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <div class="faq-q">Which platform is right for me?<span class="ic">+</span></div>
          <div class="faq-a"><p>It depends on your goals. Shopify suits most ecommerce brands, WooCommerce/WordPress fits content-heavy or flexible business sites, and Webflow is great for custom marketing sites. We'll recommend the best fit during your free audit.</p></div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <div class="faq-q">What's included in a project?<span class="ic">+</span></div>
          <div class="faq-a"><p>Everything is spelled out in the written proposal — scope, deliverables, timeline, and payment terms — so there are no surprises. Common inclusions are design, build, testing, and launch support.</p></div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <div class="faq-q">Do you offer support after launch?<span class="ic">+</span></div>
          <div class="faq-a"><p>Yes. We offer monthly care plans covering updates, backups, speed and security, content edits, and SEO improvements — so your site keeps performing after it goes live.</p></div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <div class="faq-q">How do we get started?<span class="ic">+</span></div>
          <div class="faq-a"><p>Book a free audit of your store or website. We'll review it, suggest practical improvements, and send a clear proposal if it's a good fit. No pressure either way.</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

